        content: `Kael spent his entire life operating as Niro Vane's primary shadow assassin. He was subjected to severe psychological conditioning and fed a singular narrative: *"The Kazemi family are mindless, horrific beasts who butchered your ancestors and want to devour the world."*

During a high-stakes infiltration mission near Valariya's border, Kael's deployment goes catastrophically wrong. Left broken, bleeding, and stranded inside the empire's energetic barrier, he is found and nursed back to health by **Nova Kazemi**.

Instead of a tyrannical military dictatorship, Kael experiences an organic, community-first utopia where a person's societal status is directly determined by how much they support their neighbors. He sees the legendary "Demon" Irane as a deeply broken father, self-isolated to prevent further bloodshed.

The ultimate psychological twist occurs when Kael meets **Aqura Vane** in the capital. Through her latent family bloodline senses, she detects a perfect genetic resonance. Irane uses his absolute perception to confirm the staggering reality: **Kael is the true, biological son of Lord Niro Vane.** Niro had multiple legitimate heirs but deliberately chose to hide Kael's identity, subject him to systematic emotional trauma, and turn his own flesh and blood into a disposable, brainwashed weapon.

This realization shatters Kael's remaining loyalty, providing him with a powerful legal motive: as a pure-blooded Vane, he holds the absolute biological right to return to the capital, challenge his corrupt half-siblings for succession, and claim the **Rift Cleaver (The Spatial Ripper)** for himself.`,
