        content: `**Auris** is the oldest named figure in Sol-Nexus history — an ancient Vethara who predated the Ferali/Celestials split, and the Arke twins' most powerful and trusted agent in the living world.

He was neither fully Ferali nor fully Celestials. He existed before the factions consolidated — a relic of the early Vethara, operating independently with the authority of both Arke twins behind him. His defining characteristic: **he never acted directly**. Every major event in Terra's history that served the Arke twins' interests was executed by someone else, who believed they were acting on their own ambitions.

**His Place in the Chain:**
The actual hierarchy was: Vrak and Selis Arke (Limbo, true rulers) → **Auris** (their primary agent in the world) → the 14 Gods (their direct servants) → the Vane dynasty (their mortal instrument). The 14 Gods answered to Auris. The Vane kings answered to Auris. Even the Ferali and Celestials factions' leadership deferred to Auris because he spoke with the authority of both Arke twins simultaneously.

**The Vane Front:**
The Vane dynasty — from Aevum Vane's original deal with the Arke twins through every subsequent Vane king — was Auris's managed instrument. The Vane kings believed they were serving the Celestials and Ferali. In truth, they were serving Auris, who was serving the Arke twins. Even Aevum Vane did not fully understand Auris's true authority until he figured out the slavery component of the conquest plan.

**The Uno-Reversal:**
When the subjugation ritual reached its final stage, the 14 Gods had planned to betray Auris — to eliminate him once his usefulness as an organizer was exhausted. He had been aware of this plan for decades. He waited. At the precise moment the betrayal was to be executed, Auris seized simultaneous control of all 14 God-agents present, completed the ritual himself, and established his direct authority.

He was then confronted by Irane. The details of their final battle are not preserved. What is known: Auris was killed and his spirit was **sealed into the Spear of Unix** by Irane.

*He used everyone. Now he is used.*

The Spear's power — asserting authority over all 17 other Noble Treasure wielders — is Auris's reach filtered through whoever holds the weapon. With Auris sealed and removed from the living world, the Arke twins lost their primary agent. They now operate only through the 14 Gods and what influence the Noble Treasures exert through their wielders. This is why the current era is more politically diffuse than the pre-stasis era: the Arke twins are rebuilding their influence from a distance, through instruments far less capable than Auris was.`,
